# Copy this file to .env.local and fill in the values.
# .env.local is git-ignored.

# Microsoft Azure AD application (client) ID for the DoseSync OAuth app.
# Required only if you want the Microsoft Calendar provider to work out of
# the box for end users (no manual Azure registration). Leave empty during
# development if you prefer to paste a client ID in Settings at runtime.
#
# How to register:
#   1. Go to https://entra.microsoft.com → App registrations → New registration
#   2. Name: "DoseSync"
#   3. Supported account types: "Accounts in any organizational directory and
#      personal Microsoft accounts" (multi-tenant + personal)
#   4. Redirect URI: Single-page application (SPA)
#        https://<extension-id>.chromiumapp.org/
#      (You can get the extension ID from chrome://extensions after loading
#      the unpacked build once. Both dev and prod extension IDs must be added
#      if they differ — dev IDs change with the key in manifest.json.)
#   5. After creation, copy the "Application (client) ID" from the Overview
#      page and paste it below.
#   6. Under API permissions, add Microsoft Graph delegated permissions:
#      Calendars.ReadWrite, offline_access, User.Read
VITE_MICROSOFT_CLIENT_ID=
